&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a detail-oriented and experienced finance professional to support finance operations in China.&lt;br&gt;This role will work closely with the Finance Manager and global finance team to ensure accurate financial reporting, regulatory compliance, and alignment with both PRC and global standards.&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate will bring solid accounting experience, familiarity with multinational environments, and the ability to operate effectively in a dynamic and fast-growing organization&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support day-to-day finance operations, including accounting, reporting, and financial data preparation&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Assist in the preparation of monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports (PRC GAAP and US GAAP)&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Coordinate with third-party accounting firms to ensure timely and accurate financial deliverables&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Ensure compliance with PRC tax regulations and statutory requirements&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support audit processes and liaise with auditors, tax advisors, and external stakeholders as needed&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams (R&amp;amp;D, operations, procurement) to support business activities&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Provide basic financial data and analysis to support operational needs&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support the Finance Manager in ongoing finance activities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Bachelor’s degree or above in Finance, Accounting, or related field&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;PRC CPA or equivalent qualification preferred&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;5–8 years of progressive accounting or finance experience&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Big 4 audit experience and multinational company experience preferred&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Experience in biotech, life sciences, or pharmaceutical industry is a plus&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong knowledge of PRC GAAP, with working familiarity of US GAAP&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Proficiency in English and Mandarin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong attention to detail and analytical skills&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Ability to work independently while collaborating with cross-functional teams&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Comfortable working in a fast-paced, global environment&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;High level of integrity and accountability&lt;br&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quo
